## Out of scope

If a desire surfaced during the interview that didn't make it into
the capabilities list above, it was deliberately deferred. Common
deferrals:

- "We might also want X later." → not in scope; regenerate if it
  becomes real.
- "Can it also do Y?" where Y belongs to a different archetype
  (e.g., long-form report writing in a chat-bot project). → not in
  scope; would need a separate skill.

If you discover a capability is missing during implementation, stop
and tell the user — adding capabilities mid-build expands the
`groupName` schema and the change set unpredictably.
